  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In case of CDD, multicore capability has to be ensured by implementation and design"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Methods to achieve consistency"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Avoid shared RMW data",
        "Serialize access to shared resources",
        "Partition awareness / Core dependent branching → Core specific behavior implementation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Methods"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "1. Avoid RMW data (Same Code runs in different Cores)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Each CDD BSW instance should operate on its own set of RMW (Read-Modify-Write) data, reducing the serialization to maximum"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "/confluence/download/attachments/2394061660/Avoid%20RMW%20data.png?version=3&modificationDate=1663734074000&api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/CDD for Multicore/Avoid RMW data.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Note: This approach this very difficult if MCAL runs only in BSW Core"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "2. Serialize data"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use Spinlock for shared data"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "/confluence/download/attachments/2394061660/Serialize%20data.png?version=6&modificationDate=1663734884000&api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/CDD for Multicore/Serialize data.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "3. Core specific Handling"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Core dependent branching"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Using GetCoreId() and GetApplicationId() APIs",
        "Each core invokes different APIs in one module"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Example use case for Core specific Handling:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "MCAL only in BSW Core"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the design is such a way that MCAL modules present only in BSW Core, then a satellite or proxy functions are required for CDD"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "/confluence/download/attachments/2394061660/CDD%20Proxy.png?version=5&modificationDate=1663737894000&api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/CDD for Multicore/CDD Proxy.png"
    }
  ],
